{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":999,"text":"Have you ever wondered\nwhat animals think and feel?"},{"time":5020,"text":"Let's start with a question:"},{"time":7654,"text":"Does my dog really love me,\nor does she just want a treat?"},{"time":12991,"text":"Well, it's easy to see\nthat our dog really loves us,"},{"time":17982,"text":"easy to see, right,"},{"time":20087,"text":"what's going on in that fuzzy little head."},{"time":24593,"text":"What is going on?"},{"time":27155,"text":"Something's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29864,"text":"But why is the question always\ndo they love us?"},{"time":34287,"text":"Why is it always about us?"},{"time":36422,"text":"Why are we such narcissists?"},{"time":40674,"text":"I found a different question\nto ask animals."},{"time":45911,"text":"Who are you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49910,"text":"There are capacities of the human mind"},{"time":52829,"text":"that we tend to think are capacities\nonly of the human mind."},{"time":58176,"text":"But is that true?"},{"time":60047,"text":"What are other beings\ndoing with those brains?"},{"time":64554,"text":"What are they thinking and feeling?"},{"time":67570,"text":"Is there a way to know?"},{"time":69227,"text":"I think there is a way in."},{"time":70925,"text":"I think there are several ways in."},{"time":72950,"text":"We can look at evolution,\nwe can look at their brains"},{"time":77096,"text":"and we can watch what they do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81316,"text":"The first thing to remember is:\nour brain is inherited."},{"time":86253,"text":"The first neurons came from jellyfish."},{"time":90435,"text":"Jellyfish gave rise\nto the first chordates."},{"time":93299,"text":"The first chordates gave rise\nto the first vertebrates."},{"time":97277,"text":"The vertebrates came out of the sea,"},{"time":99719,"text":"and here we are."},{"time":102737,"text":"But it's still true that a neuron,\na nerve cell, looks the same"},{"time":108351,"text":"in a crayfish, a bird or you."},{"time":112427,"text":"What does that say\nabout the minds of crayfish?"},{"time":116880,"text":"Can we tell anything about that?"},{"time":118461,"text":"Well, it turns out that\nif you give a crayfish"},{"time":122514,"text":"a lot of little tiny electric shocks"},{"time":125195,"text":"every time it tries\nto come out of its burrow,"},{"time":127515,"text":"it will develop anxiety."},{"time":131133,"text":"If you give the crayfish the same drug"},{"time":134575,"text":"used to treat anxiety disorder in humans,"},{"time":137522,"text":"it relaxes and comes out and explores."},{"time":142308,"text":"How do we show how much\nwe care about crayfish anxiety?"},{"time":145905,"text":"Mostly, we boil them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147283,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150490,"text":"Octopuses use tools,\nas well as do most apes"},{"time":155872,"text":"and they recognize human faces."},{"time":158808,"text":"How do we celebrate the ape-like\nintelligence of this invertebrate?"},{"time":163999,"text":"Mostly boiled."},{"time":166669,"text":"If a grouper chases a fish\ninto a crevice in the coral,"},{"time":170999,"text":"it will sometimes go to where it knows\na moray eel is sleeping"},{"time":175999,"text":"and it will signal\nto the moray, \"Follow me,\""},{"time":179596,"text":"and the moray will understand that signal."},{"time":182816,"text":"The moray may go into the crevice\nand get the fish,"},{"time":185817,"text":"but the fish may bolt\nand the grouper may get it."},{"time":188880,"text":"This is an ancient partnership that we\nhave just recently found out about."},{"time":194935,"text":"How do we celebrate\nthat ancient partnership?"},{"time":198044,"text":"Mostly fried."},{"time":200918,"text":"A pattern is emerging and it says\na lot more about us"},{"time":204542,"text":"than it does about them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207610,"text":"Sea otters use tools"},{"time":210039,"text":"and they take time away\nfrom what they're doing"},{"time":213040,"text":"to show their babies what to do,\nwhich is called teaching."},{"time":217205,"text":"Chimpanzees don't teach."},{"time":220999,"text":"Killer whales teach\nand killer whales share food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226879,"text":"When evolution makes something new,"},{"time":228937,"text":"it uses the parts it has\nin stock, off the shelf,"},{"time":233314,"text":"before it fabricates a new twist."},{"time":235800,"text":"And our brain has come to us"},{"time":238000,"text":"through the enormity\nof the deep sweep of time."},{"time":242425,"text":"If you look at the human brain\ncompared to a chimpanzee brain,"},{"time":246038,"text":"what you see is we have basically\na very big chimpanzee brain."},{"time":249726,"text":"It's a good thing ours is bigger,\nbecause we're also really insecure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253691,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":255777,"text":"But, uh oh, there's a dolphin,"},{"time":258917,"text":"a bigger brain with more convolutions."},{"time":262777,"text":"OK, maybe you're saying,\nall right, well, we see brains,"},{"time":265508,"text":"but what does that\nhave to say about minds?"},{"time":268347,"text":"Well, we can see the working of the mind"},{"time":272242,"text":"in the logic of behaviors."},{"time":274530,"text":"So these elephants, you can see,"},{"time":278185,"text":"obviously, they are resting."},{"time":281118,"text":"They have found a patch of shade\nunder the palm trees"},{"time":285506,"text":"under which to let their babies sleep,"},{"time":288330,"text":"while they doze but remain vigilant."},{"time":291491,"text":"We make perfect sense of that image"},{"time":294367,"text":"just as they make perfect sense\nof what they're doing"},{"time":298022,"text":"because under the arc of the same sun\non the same plains,"},{"time":301848,"text":"listening to the howls\nof the same dangers,"},{"time":305298,"text":"they became who they are\nand we became who we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310536,"text":"We've been neighbors for a very long time."},{"time":312736,"text":"No one would mistake\nthese elephants as being relaxed."},{"time":316204,"text":"They're obviously very\nconcerned about something."},{"time":319140,"text":"What are they concerned about?"},{"time":321680,"text":"It turns out that if you record\nthe voices of tourists"},{"time":325344,"text":"and you play that recording\nfrom a speaker hidden in bushes,"},{"time":330062,"text":"elephants will ignore it,\nbecause tourists never bother elephants."},{"time":334102,"text":"But if you record the voices of herders"},{"time":338868,"text":"who carry spears and often hurt elephants\nin confrontations at water holes,"},{"time":343981,"text":"the elephants will bunch up\nand run away from the hidden speaker."},{"time":348699,"text":"Not only do elephants know\nthat there are humans,"},{"time":352082,"text":"they know that there are\ndifferent kinds of humans,"},{"time":354642,"text":"and that some are OK\nand some are dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358248,"text":"They have been watching us for much longer\nthan we have been watching them."},{"time":363339,"text":"They know us better than we know them."},{"time":366272,"text":"We have the same imperatives:"},{"time":369144,"text":"take care of our babies,\nfind food, try to stay alive."},{"time":374478,"text":"Whether we're outfitted for hiking\nin the hills of Africa"},{"time":378331,"text":"or outfitted for diving under the sea,\nwe are basically the same."},{"time":382538,"text":"We are kin under the skin."},{"time":384999,"text":"The elephant has the same skeleton,"},{"time":387426,"text":"the killer whale has the same skeleton,"},{"time":389792,"text":"as do we."},{"time":393674,"text":"We see helping where help is needed."},{"time":396560,"text":"We see curiosity in the young."},{"time":400467,"text":"We see the bonds of family connections."},{"time":405776,"text":"We recognize affection."},{"time":408522,"text":"Courtship is courtship."},{"time":411999,"text":"And then we ask, \"Are they conscious?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":415300,"text":"When you get general anesthesia,\nit makes you unconscious,"},{"time":418224,"text":"which means you have\nno sensation of anything."},{"time":421083,"text":"Consciousness is simply\nthe thing that feels like something."},{"time":425292,"text":"If you see, if you hear, if you feel,\nif you're aware of anything,"},{"time":429465,"text":"you are conscious, and they are conscious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435165,"text":"Some people say"},{"time":436355,"text":"well, there are certain things\nthat make humans humans,"},{"time":438984,"text":"and one of those things is empathy."},{"time":440930,"text":"Empathy is the mind's ability\nto match moods with your companions."},{"time":447442,"text":"It's a very useful thing."},{"time":449049,"text":"If your companions start to move quickly,"},{"time":451233,"text":"you have to feel like\nyou need to hurry up."},{"time":453492,"text":"We're all in a hurry now."},{"time":455246,"text":"The oldest form of empathy\nis contagious fear."},{"time":458757,"text":"If your companions suddenly\nstartle and fly away,"},{"time":461627,"text":"it does not work very well for you to say,"},{"time":463815,"text":"\"Jeez, I wonder why everybody just left.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":466742,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":471136,"text":"Empathy is old, but empathy,\nlike everything else in life,"},{"time":474999,"text":"comes on a sliding scale\nand has its elaboration."},{"time":478934,"text":"So there's basic empathy:\nyou feel sad, it makes me sad."},{"time":482679,"text":"I see you happy, it makes me happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485192,"text":"Then there's something\nthat I call sympathy,"},{"time":487999,"text":"a little more removed:"},{"time":490365,"text":"\"I'm sorry to hear that your grandmother\nhas just passed away."},{"time":493856,"text":"I don't feel that same grief,\nbut I get it; I know what you feel"},{"time":497507,"text":"and it concerns me.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":498944,"text":"And then if we're motivated\nto act on sympathy,"},{"time":501585,"text":"I call that compassion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504061,"text":"Far from being the thing\nthat makes us human,"},{"time":507635,"text":"human empathy is far from perfect."},{"time":510999,"text":"We round up empathic creatures,\nwe kill them and we eat them."},{"time":516034,"text":"Now, maybe you say OK,\nwell, those are different species."},{"time":518925,"text":"That's just predation,\nand humans are predators."},{"time":522667,"text":"But we don't treat our own kind\ntoo well either."},{"time":529212,"text":"People who seem to know\nonly one thing about animal behavior"},{"time":532390,"text":"know that you must never attribute\nhuman thoughts and emotions"},{"time":536387,"text":"to other species."},{"time":538723,"text":"Well, I think that's silly,"},{"time":540568,"text":"because attributing human thoughts\nand emotions to other species"},{"time":544714,"text":"is the best first guess about what\nthey're doing and how they're feeling,"},{"time":548989,"text":"because their brains\nare basically the same as ours."},{"time":552326,"text":"They have the same structures."},{"time":554081,"text":"The same hormones that create\nmood and motivation in us"},{"time":559155,"text":"are in those brains as well."},{"time":563050,"text":"It is not scientific to say that they\nare hungry when they're hunting"},{"time":568144,"text":"and they're tired when\ntheir tongues are hanging out,"},{"time":571115,"text":"and then say when they're playing\nwith their children"},{"time":573829,"text":"and acting joyful and happy,"},{"time":575764,"text":"we have no idea if they can possibly\nbe experiencing anything."},{"time":580577,"text":"That is not scientific."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583619,"text":"So OK, so a reporter said to me,"},{"time":586328,"text":"\"Maybe, but how do you really know\nthat other animals can think and feel?\""},{"time":590660,"text":"And I started to rifle\nthrough all the hundreds"},{"time":593739,"text":"of scientific references\nthat I put in my book"},{"time":596262,"text":"and I realized that the answer\nwas right in the room with me."},{"time":599526,"text":"When my dog gets off the rug\nand comes over to me --"},{"time":603303,"text":"not to the couch, to me --"},{"time":605089,"text":"and she rolls over on her back\nand exposes her belly,"},{"time":609290,"text":"she has had the thought,\n\"I would like my belly rubbed."},{"time":614565,"text":"I know that I can go over to Carl,"},{"time":617125,"text":"he will understand what I'm asking."},{"time":620084,"text":"I know I can trust him\nbecause we're family."},{"time":623406,"text":"He'll get the job done,\nand it will feel good.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":626145,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628055,"text":"She has thought and she has felt,"},{"time":631408,"text":"and it's really not\nmore complicated than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634096,"text":"But we see other animals\nand we say, \"Oh look, killer whales,"},{"time":638733,"text":"wolves, elephants:"},{"time":641167,"text":"that's not how they see it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":643714,"text":"That tall-finned male is L41."},{"time":648032,"text":"He's 38 years old."},{"time":650103,"text":"The female right on his left side is L22."},{"time":653899,"text":"She's 44."},{"time":655475,"text":"They've known each other for decades."},{"time":658650,"text":"They know exactly who they are."},{"time":660646,"text":"They know who their friends are."},{"time":662221,"text":"They know who their rivals are."},{"time":663943,"text":"Their life follows the arc of a career."},{"time":666802,"text":"They know where they are all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670863,"text":"This is an elephant named Philo."},{"time":673667,"text":"He was a young male."},{"time":675519,"text":"This is him four days later."},{"time":678999,"text":"Humans not only can feel grief,\nwe create an awful lot of it."},{"time":686648,"text":"We want to carve their teeth."},{"time":690153,"text":"Why can't we wait for them to die?"},{"time":695998,"text":"Elephants once ranged from the shores\nof the Mediterranean Sea"},{"time":699490,"text":"all the way down to the Cape of Good Hope."},{"time":701589,"text":"In 1980, there were vast\nstrongholds of elephant range"},{"time":704999,"text":"in Central and Eastern Africa."},{"time":707211,"text":"And now their range is shattered\ninto little shards."},{"time":711572,"text":"This is the geography of an animal\nthat we are driving to extinction,"},{"time":716275,"text":"a fellow being, the most\nmagnificent creature on land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721288,"text":"Of course, we take much better care\nof our wildlife in the United States."},{"time":725681,"text":"In Yellowstone National Park,\nwe killed every single wolf."},{"time":729940,"text":"We killed every single wolf\nsouth of the Canadian border, actually."},{"time":733413,"text":"But in the park, park rangers\ndid that in the 1920s,"},{"time":737830,"text":"and then 60 years later\nthey had to bring them back,"},{"time":740445,"text":"because the elk numbers\nhad gotten out of control."},{"time":744511,"text":"And then people came."},{"time":745809,"text":"People came by the thousands\nto see the wolves,"},{"time":749557,"text":"the most accessibly\nvisible wolves in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753512,"text":"And I went there and I watched\nthis incredible family of wolves."},{"time":756788,"text":"A pack is a family."},{"time":758265,"text":"It has some breeding adults\nand the young of several generations."},{"time":763158,"text":"And I watched the most famous, most stable\npack in Yellowstone National Park."},{"time":768370,"text":"And then, when they wandered\njust outside the border,"},{"time":771524,"text":"two of their adults were killed,"},{"time":774229,"text":"including the mother,"},{"time":776506,"text":"which we sometimes call the alpha female."},{"time":779502,"text":"The rest of the family immediately\ndescended into sibling rivalry."},{"time":784871,"text":"Sisters kicked out other sisters."},{"time":787565,"text":"That one on the left tried for days\nto rejoin her family."},{"time":791070,"text":"They wouldn't let her\nbecause they were jealous of her."},{"time":793786,"text":"She was getting too much attention\nfrom two new males,"},{"time":796623,"text":"and she was the precocious one."},{"time":798665,"text":"That was too much for them."},{"time":800342,"text":"She wound up wandering\noutside the park and getting shot."},{"time":804463,"text":"The alpha male wound up\nbeing ejected from his own family."},{"time":808436,"text":"As winter was coming in,"},{"time":810463,"text":"he lost his territory,\nhis hunting support,"},{"time":814237,"text":"the members of his family and his mate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818883,"text":"We cause so much pain to them."},{"time":823665,"text":"The mystery is, why don't\nthey hurt us more than they do?"},{"time":829855,"text":"This whale had just finished eating\npart of a grey whale"},{"time":833077,"text":"with his companions\nwho had killed that whale."},{"time":835680,"text":"Those people in the boat\nhad nothing at all to fear."},{"time":839999,"text":"This whale is T20."},{"time":842488,"text":"He had just finished tearing a seal\ninto three pieces with two companions."},{"time":847168,"text":"The seal weighed about as much\nas the people in the boat."},{"time":849884,"text":"They had nothing to fear."},{"time":852189,"text":"They eat seals."},{"time":854699,"text":"Why don't they eat us?"},{"time":858823,"text":"Why can we trust them around our toddlers?"},{"time":864488,"text":"Why is it that killer whales have returned\nto researchers lost in thick fog"},{"time":870414,"text":"and led them miles until the fog parted"},{"time":873768,"text":"and the researchers' home\nwas right there on the shoreline?"},{"time":876957,"text":"And that's happened more than one time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881171,"text":"In the Bahamas, there's a woman\nnamed Denise Herzing,"},{"time":883770,"text":"and she studies spotted dolphins\nand they know her."},{"time":887118,"text":"She knows them very well.\nShe knows who they all are."},{"time":889740,"text":"They know her.\nThey recognize the research boat."},{"time":892026,"text":"When she shows up,\nit's a big happy reunion."},{"time":894280,"text":"Except, one time showed up and they\ndidn't want to come near the boat,"},{"time":897619,"text":"and that was really strange."},{"time":899717,"text":"And they couldn't figure out\nwhat was going on"},{"time":901905,"text":"until somebody came out on deck"},{"time":903429,"text":"and announced that one\nof the people onboard had died"},{"time":906088,"text":"during a nap in his bunk."},{"time":908740,"text":"How could dolphins know\nthat one of the human hearts"},{"time":912690,"text":"had just stopped?"},{"time":914818,"text":"Why would they care?"},{"time":917132,"text":"And why would it spook them?"},{"time":921111,"text":"These mysterious things just hint at\nall of the things that are going on"},{"time":926434,"text":"in the minds that are with us on Earth"},{"time":929200,"text":"that we almost never think about at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":934258,"text":"At an aquarium in South Africa"},{"time":936454,"text":"was a little baby bottle-nosed\ndolphin named Dolly."},{"time":940178,"text":"She was nursing, and one day\na keeper took a cigarette break"},{"time":946346,"text":"and he was looking into the window\ninto their pool, smoking."},{"time":950477,"text":"Dolly came over and looked at him,"},{"time":952875,"text":"went back to her mother,\nnursed for a minute or two,"},{"time":956777,"text":"came back to the window"},{"time":958604,"text":"and released a cloud of milk\nthat enveloped her head like smoke."},{"time":964293,"text":"Somehow, this baby bottle-nosed dolphin"},{"time":967423,"text":"got the idea of using milk\nto represent smoke."},{"time":972211,"text":"When human beings use one thing\nto represent another,"},{"time":975583,"text":"we call that art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977632,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":979679,"text":"The things that make us human"},{"time":981234,"text":"are not the things\nthat we think make us human."},{"time":984781,"text":"What makes us human is that,"},{"time":987129,"text":"of all these things that our minds\nand their minds have,"},{"time":990289,"text":"we are the most extreme."},{"time":994347,"text":"We are the most compassionate,"},{"time":996660,"text":"most violent, most creative"},{"time":999701,"text":"and most destructive animal\nthat has ever been on this planet,"},{"time":1004385,"text":"and we are all of those things\nall jumbled up together."},{"time":1009341,"text":"But love is not the thing\nthat makes us human."},{"time":1014242,"text":"It's not special to us."},{"time":1017674,"text":"We are not the only ones\nwho care about our mates."},{"time":1021669,"text":"We are not the only ones\nwho care about our children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026904,"text":"Albatrosses frequently fly six,\nsometimes ten thousand miles"},{"time":1031898,"text":"over several weeks to deliver\none meal, one big meal,"},{"time":1036409,"text":"to their chick who is waiting for them."},{"time":1038835,"text":"They nest on the most remote islands\nin the oceans of the world,"},{"time":1043257,"text":"and this is what it looks like."},{"time":1047370,"text":"Passing life from one generation\nto the next is the chain of being."},{"time":1051574,"text":"If that stops, it all goes away."},{"time":1054975,"text":"If anything is sacred, that is,\nand into that sacred relationship"},{"time":1059649,"text":"comes our plastic trash."},{"time":1062504,"text":"All of these birds\nhave plastic in them now."},{"time":1065990,"text":"This is an albatross six months old,\nready to fledge --"},{"time":1070665,"text":"died, packed with red cigarette lighters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074690,"text":"This is not the relationship\nwe are supposed to have"},{"time":1077999,"text":"with the rest of the world."},{"time":1079609,"text":"But we, who have named\nourselves after our brains,"},{"time":1084195,"text":"never think about the consequences."},{"time":1089041,"text":"When we welcome new\nhuman life into the world,"},{"time":1092185,"text":"we welcome our babies\ninto the company of other creatures."},{"time":1096712,"text":"We paint animals on the walls."},{"time":1098829,"text":"We don't paint cell phones."},{"time":1100681,"text":"We don't paint work cubicles."},{"time":1102848,"text":"We paint animals to show them\nthat we are not alone."},{"time":1107316,"text":"We have company."},{"time":1110527,"text":"And every one of those animals\nin every painting of Noah's ark,"},{"time":1115291,"text":"deemed worthy of salvation\nis in mortal danger now,"},{"time":1119655,"text":"and their flood is us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1123704,"text":"So we started with a question:"},{"time":1126027,"text":"Do they love us?"},{"time":1129999,"text":"We're going to ask another question."},{"time":1132999,"text":"Are we capable of using what we have"},{"time":1137918,"text":"to care enough to simply\nlet them continue?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1144725,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1146090,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}